Compare.graph_title: Trends in Carbon Monoxide Hospitalizations - Other Causes - Age-Adjusted Rate 2000 to 2013

info.info_how_calculated: Number of NYC resident hospitalizations containing ICD-9 diagnosis code for carbon monoxide poisoning, 986, or any of the following: E868.2, E868.3, E868.8, E868.9. Must not have any fire-related injury code E890.0-E899.9, nor any intentional injury code E950.0-E969. Acceptable injury codes in range: E800.0-E888.9, E900.0-E909.9. Counts are summed by 5-year age groups and divided by the population in each age group, using NYC DOHMH intercensal estimates; quotients are multiplied by the proportion of the 2000 US population in each age group. Age-adjusted rate is the sum of the weighted age-specific rates; expressed as cases per million residents.
info.info_source: New York State Statewide Planning and Research Cooperative System (SPARCS) Deidentified Hospital Discharge Data
